le</strong>. It\'s like giving it superpowers.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<code>chmod +x post-receive</code>\r\n\r\n 	<li>Now you can bail out of the server! Woot! Until we meet again, Skymaster. Until we meet again.Back in your local project, you\'ll need to <strong>add a remote connection</strong> to your site. It will look something like this:\r\n\r\n<code>git remote add dreamhost ssh://your_username@your_site_name.wahetever/home/your_username/repo/kittens.git</code>\r\n\r\nI know.\r\n\r\nThen - you\'ll <strong>push up those files</strong>!\r\n\r\n<code>git push dreamhost master</code>\r\n\r\nThen you dance!!!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis is only half of the equation, of course - in order to fully migrate your site, you\'ll also need to move over your database - but the point here is, folks - that you can now deploy your file changes using Git instead of stupid SFTP and you will feel like a total badass.\r\n\r\nSKYMASTERRRRRRRRRR!!!','Dreamhost and Git - how to deploy from local to live.','You have a local project, you\'ve put it under version control and now you want to use Git\'s awesome powers to push all of your files over to your live site - because SFTP blows. ','inherit','closed','closed','','47838-revision-v1','','','2017-05-29 16:42:50','2017-05-29 16:42:50','',47838,'https://redrambles.blog//47838-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(47858,1,'2017-05-29 18:37:56','2017-05-29 18:37:56','You have a local project, you\'ve put it under version control and now you want to use Git\'s awesome powers to push all of your files over to your live site - because SFTP blows. Right?! Dreamhost say that they support Git, so I figured - righto - let\'s get this show on the road!\r\n\r\nEhhhhhh - This is where things got murky - at least for me. The documentation I unearthed was incomplete at best. Though Git <strong>is</strong> already installed on my Dreamhost server, that was pretty much the end of git support, at least in so far as I found. (sad emoji)\r\n\r\nSo! I decided